1. Unzip folder and build project using following maven comman
mvn -e clean install

2. Run TwitterCollector.scala to collect tweets. It will save tweets in D:/tmp/tweets_out with folder structures corresponding to every hour of a day.
3. Following system environment variables can be set and are used in TwitterCollector.scala
    OUTPUT_DIR : Specify Output directory
    OUTPUT_BATCH_INTERVAL :  Size of output batches in seconds
    OUTPUT_FILES : Number of output files per batch interval.

4. Run FileDataAnalyzer.scala to run analysis on data collected in step 1.

5. Run TwitterCollectorAnalyzer.scala to run analysis on real-time tweets.


Input file folder link : https://drive.google.com/open?id=1wqAmw5sHITmU1kqsYzA7in4brOkijeUp
Historical Analysis Output files : https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1vbHV2RjlQ0JTYmCh--dSp60SAF5fXUB9

real-time Analysis Output files : https://drive.google.com/open?id=12XJ1Vz0GnK7t3pqSD9bp3JUteSYMsHOt
